# NetworkSniffer
Advanced Network Packet Sniffer

A Python-based network packet sniffer built using Scapy that captures and analyzes live network traffic in real-time. This project logs packet details such as IP addresses, protocol types, ports, and payload data.

🚀 Features
📥 Capture live network packets
🌐 Extract Source & Destination IP addresses
🔢 Identify protocol types (TCP, UDP, ICMP, Others)
🔌 Display port information for TCP/UDP
📦 View partial payload data
🕒 Timestamp each packet
📝 Save logs to a file (packet_log.txt)
📊 Count total packets captured
🛠️ Technologies Used
Python 3
Scapy Library
Socket Programming
Datetime Module
